<h2 id="your-basic-slide">Your basic slide</h2>

<p>First things first, you need a basic slide. The design of these slides is about lessening the impact of things that go wrong with technology.</p>

<p>Iâ€™ve used a system font so that if I have to present off someone elseâ€™s computer, theyâ€™ll definitely have the font installed and my formatting wonâ€™t unexpectedly break.</p>

<p>Most of these slides use a dark on light design so that if the projector is terrible and the room is really bright, youâ€™ll still be able to read them. <a href="http://rmurphey.com/blog/2012/11/29/choosing-presentation-color-scheme">Rebecca Murphey has a good post on this</a>.</p>

<p>Iâ€™ve used big margins at the left, right and top so if the projector isnâ€™t lined up properly with the screen none of my important words will go missing.</p>

<p>In case someone comes in half way through, put some way of finding out who you are (your name or Twitter handle) on the slide.</p>

