<h2 id="a-blank-slide">A blank slide</h2>

<p>My keynote theme has a completely blank slide for charts and diagrams. Charts and diagrams are where even good presenters can get into trouble. My only advice is make your labels as big as possible, and think carefully about what youâ€™re trying to show. People looking at a chart or diagram in a report have more time to pore over it than they do when looking at your slide in a presentation. Manage your audienceâ€™s focus by highlighting the important bits of a chart, and obscuring the other bits.</p>

<p><img src="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/slides-blog-post/blank.jpeg" alt="Your basic slide with image" /></p>

<h2 id="your-title-slide">Your title slide</h2>

<p>Itâ€™s a really really good idea to have a title slide. It means that while youâ€™re futzing around with the presenter display in the pre-talk bit the audience isnâ€™t reading your slides, theyâ€™re just looking at your name and the title of your talk. Again, give people a way to find out more about you and what youâ€™re talking about.</p>

